569  /-- A family of elements of α is directed (with respect to a relation `≼` on α)
570    if there is a member of the family `≼`-above any pair in the family.  -/
571  def directed {ι : Sort v} (f : ι → α) := ∀x y, ∃z, f x ≼ f z ∧ f y ≼ f z

572  /-- A subset of α is directed if there is an element of the set `≼`-above any
573    pair of elements in the set. -/
574  def directed_on (s : set α) := ∀ (x ∈ s) (y ∈ s), ∃z ∈ s, x ≼ z ∧ y ≼ z
